From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:04:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 34/64] web-app: hover popovers with avatars for read-by status
 and reactions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Reveal a small popover when hovering the "read" delivery-status icon or a
message's reactions, so the "who read this / who reacted" information is
available without opening the Message Info or Reactions dialog.

- Read-by: hovering the delivery-status icon of a read outgoing message
  shows the contacts who have read it, each with their avatar, name and a
  relative timestamp ("2 minutes ago"); the absolute time is on the row's
  title. Only the "read" state gets the popover — other delivery states
  keep the plain icon. Data comes from getMessageReadReceipts and
  refreshes on the MsgRead event, and is only fetched once the popover is
  first opened.
- Reactions: each reaction pill is its own hover target — hovering one
  emoji lists just the people who reacted with it, while the "+N"
  overflow pill lists the remaining (mixed) reactions with each reactor's
  emoji. Clicking still opens the full ReactionsDialog.

Adds an `xSmall` (24px) variant to the shared Avatar component and uses
it for the compact popover rows. The popover nudges itself back into the
viewport when it would overflow an edge (e.g. the "+N" pill of a
right-aligned message). Adds the untranslated label "Reacted with %1$s".

Popover rows are `<div role="listitem">` inside a `<div role="list">`,
not real `<ul>`/`<li>` elements: this card can render anywhere in the
app — including inside the message list's own `<ol>` — and upstream's
`ol li` styling (margins, min-width, a clearfix) would otherwise bleed
onto genuine `<li>`s no matter how specifically we scope our own class.

Both share a new PeopleHoverInfo component (the hover trigger, the card
shell, a lazy contacts-by-id fetch and a relative-time helper).
